{
  "texts": [
    "In relation to the second theme: what is commented on in feedback, 42.1% of the participants indicated that three key factors contributed to effective and personalised feedback: 1.",
    "Identifying knowledge gaps to specify clear areas where students lack understanding or skills as this helps them know exactly where they need to focus their efforts to improve; 2.",
    "Providing clear comments to note the strengths and weaknesses in the students' work to help students understand what they did well and where they need to improve; 3.",
    "Guidance or suggestions for improvement, which can involve suggesting resources, providing lists of ideas, examples, and suggesting specific steps for students to take to address areas in which they fall short.",
    "One participant, Reese, offered this perspective:"
  ]
}